OL,3,CPublic 'deserve better' as millions
OL,4,Cwasted on IT, top civil servant says
OL,6,FGuernsey's most senior civil servant
OL,7,Fsays the public and frontline staff
OL,8,F"deserve better" after the Deputy
OL,9,FChief Minister publicly revealed that
OL,10,Fan #18 million government project to
OL,11,Fdigitise services has "delivered
OL,12,Fnothing of any substance" and is an
OL,13,F"unconscionable waste of public money".
OL,15,FStates' Chief Executive Boley Smillie
OL,16,Ftook up his role at the start of the
OL,17,Fyear and has since advised the
OL,18,Fisland's top political committee "of
OL,19,Fhis serious concerns about the way
OL,20,Fmajor projects have been managed over
OL,21,Fmany years".
