OL,3,CPublic 'deserve better' as millions
OL,4,Cwasted on IT, top civil servant says
OL,6,FOn the Revenue Service upgrade, Deputy
OL,7,FSt Pier added: "The States have ended
OL,8,Fup with a system that is not yet
OL,9,Fcomplete, has reduced functionality,
OL,10,Fprovides poor service levels for
OL,11,Fcustomers, and seems to be a system
OL,12,Fwith a limited lifespan.
OL,14,F"Depressingly, it seems that the
OL,15,Fissues with major programmes are not
OL,16,Fisolated to the Revenue Service
OL,17,FTransformation programme - they appear
OL,18,Fto reflect structural and cultural
OL,19,Fproblems that have undermined the
OL,20,Feffectiveness of other major
OL,21,Fprogrammes.
