OL,3,CPublic 'deserve better' as millions
OL,4,Cwasted on IT, top civil servant says
OL,6,FSome people have struggled to complete
OL,7,Ftheir 2024 tax returns due to
OL,8,Fintermittent issues with the Revenue
OL,9,FService's online portal, and the
OL,10,Fdeadline for submissions has now been
OL,11,Fextended to Saturday, 31 January 2026.
OL,13,FHowever, Nig Garland, Acting Director
OL,14,Fof the Revenue Service, says: "While
OL,15,Fthe deadline has been extended,
OL,16,Fcustomers are encouraged to file as
OL,17,Fearly as possible to help reduce
OL,18,Fpressure on the system and support a
OL,19,Fsmoother flow of processing and
OL,20,Fassistance."
